from caldwell larry caldwell subject re merlin mithra and magick in response to whitten david whitten i write there evidently wa a feast of bread and wine associate with mithra i have often wonder if yeshua intentionally introduce thi ritual to expand the appeal of hi religion or if it wa appropriate by later worshiper and you respond you could argue that if you want but i think a more reasonable argument would point out the fact that the remembrance feast wa very similar to the pesach passover meal during seder a very jewish ritual of course the feast wa the seder and the account of it be very clear on thi point the difference be the connection between the bread and wine and the body and blood of god thi be an old association of the line and not really relate to judaism in any case i do really intend to argue the point i saw a possible association and point it out but i have the foggiest notion what really happen larry caldwell caldwell compuserve oregon health science university 